Subject: Marching bands $z California $z Los Angeles County
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Department of Special Collections
Rights.rightsHolderContact: UCLA Charles E. Young Research Library Department of Special Collections, A1713 Young Research Library, Box 951575, Los Angeles, CA 90095-1575. E-mail: spec-coll@library.ucla.edu. Phone: (310)825-4988
Relation.isPartOf: Los Angeles Times Photographic Archive. Department of Special Collections, Charles E. Young Research Library, UCLA.
Description.note: Duplicate of 21198/zz002hj86f|~|Views of a marching band on a football field. There are eighteen images on one contact sheet. The images include ten oblique views of the band in a single-line formation, with the drumline on the left; six views of a short female band member holding her large hat and looking up at a tall male trumpet player, standing facing each other in profile, with a building visible in the background; and two images of a female band member in the drumline playing a snare drum. The band uniform consists of a light-colored shirt (satin?) with wide, cuffed sleeves; dark trousers with a light-colored stripe down the side of the leg; and hat with tall, prominent plumes.
Title: Contact sheet with images of a marching band on a football field, Los Angeles County, 1940s-1960s (?)
